wi_steps.step_desc:
Prepare the components listed:
- 1) Hub front x2
- 2) Hub rear x2
- 3) Bush x4
- 4) Cv joints x4
- 5) Link upper front x2
- 6) Link upper rear x2
- 7) Rim x4
- 8) Rim protector x4 (It is most likely already been attached to the rim)
- 9) Tyre x4
- S1. Screw (d) 2.6mm (l) 11mm x4
- S2. Washer screw (od) 6mm (id) 2.6mm (l) 9mm x4

1) Remove the rim protector from the rim, for all 4 rims.

Check next step for removing the rim protector.

2) Hold part No. 8 with all 4 fingers as shown in the image on the left.
3) Push part No. 7 using thumb while the other finger holds firmly.

CAUTION THE RIM PROTECTOR HOLDS THE RIM TIGHTLY.

4) Put on the tyre for all 4 rims.

You can look at the direction of the tyre pattern for better looking.

5) Take note of the difference between the front and the rear hub.
6) Insert the Cv joint into all 4 hubs.

7) Notice that the rim's hole is a hexagon
8) Insert the hub and Cv joint into the hole of the rim. IF IT DOESN'T FIT ROTATE THE RIM CLOCKWISE OR COUNTERCLOCKWISE.

9) Hold down the cv joints firmly.
10) Screw it from the outer surface of the rim using S2, do this for all 4 rims.
11) S1 is longer than S2, S2 have greater outer diameter than S1.

13) Prepare these two sets of components, the front wheel will have a longer red component (part No. 5) and the rear wheel will have a shorter red component (part No. 6).
14) The component in the yellow box will be thicker for front wheel and thinner for rear wheel.
15) Place part No. 3 into one of the sides of part No. 5 and part No. 6.

16) Connect the outer parts of part No. 1 and part No. 2 to the red component while the bush faces upward.
17) Scew it with S1 and make sure it is TIGHTENED. When screwing make sure that you hold part No. 1 or part No. 2 firmly. (Push the screwdriver a bit when screwing)

Do this for both the front and rear wheels.

PLEASE BE PATIENCE!!

18) It should look like this.
19) Make sure the component used is correct, if not sure please refer back to STEP 9.
